\subsection{Inclusion of level 2 fields}

We have carried out the same kind of analysis as in the previous
subsection by including the level two fields.
Taking into account of spatial rotational symmetry,
twist symmetry and the invariance under $X\to -X$ \cite{lump2},
the string field $\vert \Phi\rangle=b_0\vert \phi\rangle$ in the Siegel gauge
with component fields up to level two is expanded as
follows:
\begin{align}
\vert \phi(x^0)\rangle=& \vert 0\rangle\, t(x^0)+c_{-1}b_{-1}\vert 0\rangle\, u(x^0)
-\frac12 \left(\alpha_{-1}^0\right)^2 \vert 0\rangle\, v(x^0)\nonumber\\
&\qquad\qquad\qquad - i\,\alpha_{-2}^0\vert 0\rangle\,\chi(x^0)
+\frac12\alpha_{-1}^i\alpha_{-1}^i\vert 0\rangle\, w(x^0),
\end{align}
where $t$, $u$, $v$ and $w$ are even functions of $x^0$ and hence
are expanded by $\cosh nx^0$; $\varphi(x^0)=\sum_{n=0}^\infty
\varphi_n \cosh nx^0$ ($\varphi=t$, $u$, $v$, $w$), while $\chi$ is an
odd function and is expanded by $\sinh nx^0$;
$\chi(x^0)=\sum_{n=1}^\infty\chi_n\sinh nx^0$.
These five fields are all hermitian.
We have used the level $(2,6)$ action\footnote{
Here, we assign level zero to $t_n$ and level two to
$u_n$, $v_n$, $\chi_n$ and $w_n$ for all $n$.
}
in our calculation.

In this numerical analysis, we adopted $N=30$ as the cutoff of the
mode number $n$ for all the five fields and solved the equation of
motion of each mode for a given value of $t_1$.
Then, fitting the solution $t_n(t_1)$ by \eqref{tnfit}, we obtained
$\xi(t_1)$ and $\beta(t_1)$, which are shown in figs.\ \ref{xi3030}
and \ref{beta3030}.\footnote{
